<TITLE> Education spending pushed up to Tk 179.59bn </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)--Education is being prioritised with a Tk 179.59 billion allocation in the upcoming fiscal year. Finance minister AMA Muhith placed the budget proposal for 2010-2011 fiscal year at the parliament on Thursday. The allocation consists of Tk 98.8532 billion for the education ministry to fund both its development and non-development initiatives, seeing a rise of 10 percent from the current fiscal year. Primary and mass education ministry is to receive Tk 80.74 billion which is 18 percent more than the ongoing year. The sector's total allocations increased by 13.5 percent in contrast to the Tk 158.2 billion revised budgetary allocation of 2009-10 FY. The finance minister said, the current government is taking all sort of steps to build a corruption free, clear, efficient and speedy education system. bdnew
